file.content:
openapi: 3.0.0
info:
  description: Azure Log Analytics API reference for LinkTargets, StorageInsightConfigs and
    SavedSearches.
  title: Azure Log Analytics
  version: 2015-03-20
  x-apisguru-categories:
    - cloud
  x-logo:
    url: https://assets.onestore.ms/cdnfiles/onestorerolling-1606-01000/shell/v3/images/logo/microsoft.png
  x-origin:
    - format: swagger
      url: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Azure/azure-rest-api-specs/master/specification/operationalinsights/resource-manager/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/stable/2015-03-20/OperationalInsights.json
      version: "2.0"
  x-preferred: false
  x-providerName: azure.com
  x-serviceName: operationalinsights-OperationalInsights
  x-tags:
    - Azure
    - Microsoft
security:
  - azure_auth:
      - user_impersonation
paths:
  /providers/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/operations:
    get:
      description: Lists all of the available OperationalInsights Rest API operations.
      operationId: Operations_List
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK response definition.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/OperationListResult"
              examples:
                OperationsList:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/OperationsList"
      tags:
        - Operations
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/providers/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/linkTargets":
    get:
      description: Get a list of workspaces which the current user has administrator
        privileges and are not associated with an Azure Subscription. The
        subscriptionId parameter in the Url is ignored.
      operationId: Workspaces_ListLinkTargets
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK response definition.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                items:
                  $ref: "#/components/schemas/LinkTarget"
                type: array
              examples:
                LinkTargetsList:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/LinkTargetsList"
      tags:
        - Workspaces
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/{workspaceName}/operations/{purgeId}":
    get:
      description: Gets status of an ongoing purge operation.
      operationId: Workspaces_GetPurgeStatus
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspacePurgeIdParameter"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: "Returns status of purge operation in body of response.
            e.g.:  running, completed."
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/WorkspacePurgeStatusResponse"
              examples:
                WorkspacePurgeOperation:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/WorkspacePurgeOperation"
      tags:
        - Workspaces
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/{workspaceName}/purge":
    post:
      description: Purges data in an Log Analytics workspace by a set of user-defined
        filters.
      operationId: Workspaces_Purge
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
      requestBody:
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: "#/components/schemas/WorkspacePurgeBody"
        description: Describes the body of a request to purge data in a single table of an
          Log Analytics Workspace
        required: true
        x-ms-parameter-location: client
      responses:
        "202":
          description: Accepted request for purging an Log Analytics workspace.
          headers:
            x-ms-status-location:
              description: The location from which to request the operation status.
              schema:
                type: string
              example: https://management.azure.com/subscriptions/b96161de-b34a-480f-7343-59b099299283/resourceGroups/example/providers/microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces/test/operations/purge-970318e7-b859-4edb-8903-83b1b54d0b74?api-version=2015-03-20
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/WorkspacePurgeResponse"
              examples:
                WorkspacePurge:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/WorkspacePurge"
      tags:
        - Workspaces
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourcegroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/{workspaceName}/gateways/{gatewayId}":
    delete:
      description: Delete a Log Analytics gateway.
      operationId: Workspaces_DeleteGateways
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/GatewayIdParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: The specified gateway was deleted successfully.
      tags:
        - Workspaces
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourcegroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/{workspaceName}/listKeys":
    post:
      description: Gets the shared keys for a Log Analytics Workspace. These keys are used
        to connect Microsoft Operational Insights agents to the workspace.
      operationId: Workspaces_ListKeys
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Returns the shared keys associated with the Log Analytics Workspace.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/SharedKeys"
              examples:
                SharedKeysList:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/SharedKeysList"
      tags:
        - Workspaces
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourcegroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/{workspaceName}/regenerateSharedKey":
    post:
      description: Regenerates the shared keys for a Log Analytics Workspace. These keys
        are used to connect Microsoft Operational Insights agents to the
        workspace.
      operationId: Workspaces_RegenerateSharedKeys
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Returns the new shared keys associated with the Log Analytics
            Workspace.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/SharedKeys"
              examples:
                RegenerateSharedKeys:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/RegenerateSharedKeys"
      tags:
        - Workspaces
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourcegroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/{workspaceName}/savedSearches":
    get:
      description: Gets the saved searches for a given Log Analytics Workspace
      operationId: SavedSearches_ListByWorkspace
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Returns the list of saved searches for the given Log Analytics
            Workspace.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/SavedSearchesListResult"
              examples:
                SavedSearchesList:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/SavedSearchesList"
      tags:
        - SavedSearches
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourcegroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/{workspaceName}/savedSearches/{savedSearchId}":
    delete:
      description: Deletes the specified saved search in a given workspace.
      operationId: SavedSearches_Delete
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
        - description: The id of the saved search.
          in: path
          name: savedSearchId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            SavedSearchesDelete:
              value: 00000000-0000-0000-0000-00000000000
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK response definition.
      tags:
        - SavedSearches
    get:
      description: Gets the specified saved search for a given workspace.
      operationId: SavedSearches_Get
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
        - description: The id of the saved search.
          in: path
          name: savedSearchId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            SavedSearchesGet:
              value: 00000000-0000-0000-0000-00000000000
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK response definition.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/SavedSearch"
              examples:
                SavedSearchesGet:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/SavedSearchesGet"
      tags:
        - SavedSearches
    put:
      description: Creates or updates a saved search for a given workspace.
      operationId: SavedSearches_CreateOrUpdate
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
        - description: The id of the saved search.
          in: path
          name: savedSearchId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            SavedSearchCreateOrUpdate:
              value: 00000000-0000-0000-0000-00000000000
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
      requestBody:
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: "#/components/schemas/SavedSearch"
        description: The parameters required to save a search.
        required: true
      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK response definition.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/SavedSearch"
              examples:
                SavedSearchCreateOrUpdate:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/SavedSearchCreateOrUpdate"
      tags:
        - SavedSearches
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourcegroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/{workspaceName}/savedSearches/{savedSearchId}/results":
    get:
      description: Gets the results from a saved search for a given workspace.
      operationId: SavedSearches_GetResults
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
        - description: The id of the saved search.
          in: path
          name: savedSearchId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            SaveSearchesListResults:
              value: 00000000-0000-0000-0000-00000000000
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK response definition.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/SearchResultsResponse"
              examples:
                SaveSearchesListResults:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/SaveSearchesListResults"
      tags:
        - SavedSearches
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourcegroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/{workspaceName}/schema":
    post:
      description: Gets the schema for a given workspace.
      operationId: Workspaces_GetSchema
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK response definition.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/SearchGetSchemaResponse"
              examples:
                WorkspacesGetSchema:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/WorkspacesGetSchema"
      tags:
        - Workspaces
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourcegroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/{workspaceName}/search":
    post:
      description: "Submit a search for a given workspace. The response will contain an id
        to track the search. User can use the id to poll the search status and
        get the full search result later if the search takes long time to
        finish. "
      operationId: Workspaces_GetSearchResults
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
      requestBody:
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: "#/components/schemas/SearchParameters"
        description: The parameters required to execute a search query.
        required: true
      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK response definition.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/SearchResultsResponse"
              examples:
                WorkspacesGetSearchResults:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/WorkspacesGetSearchResults"
        "202":
          description: Accepted response definition
      tags:
        - Workspaces
      x-ms-long-running-operation: true
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourcegroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/{workspaceName}/search/{id}":
    post:
      description: Gets updated search results for a given search query.
      operationId: Workspaces_UpdateSearchResults
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
        - description: The id of the search that will have results updated. You can get the
            id from the response of the GetResults call.
          in: path
          name: id
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            WorkspacesUpdateSearchResults:
              value: SavedSearchName
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK response definition.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/SearchResultsResponse"
      tags:
        - Workspaces
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourcegroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/{workspaceName}/storageInsightConfigs":
    get:
      description: Lists the storage insight instances within a workspace
      operationId: StorageInsights_ListByWorkspace
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK response definition.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/StorageInsightListResult"
              examples:
                StorageInsightsList:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/StorageInsightsList"
      tags:
        - StorageInsights
      x-ms-pageable:
        nextLinkName: "@odata.nextLink"
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourcegroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/{workspaceName}/storageInsightConfigs/{storageInsightName}":
    delete:
      description: Deletes a storageInsightsConfigs resource
      operationId: StorageInsights_Delete
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
        - description: Name of the storageInsightsConfigs resource
          in: path
          name: storageInsightName
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            StorageInsightsDelete:
              value: AzTestSI1110
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK response definition.
        "204":
          description: NoContent response definition.
      tags:
        - StorageInsights
    get:
      description: Gets a storage insight instance.
      operationId: StorageInsights_Get
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
        - description: Name of the storageInsightsConfigs resource
          in: path
          name: storageInsightName
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            StorageInsightsGet:
              value: AzTestSI1110
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK response definition.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/StorageInsight"
              examples:
                StorageInsightsGet:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/StorageInsightsGet"
      tags:
        - StorageInsights
    put:
      description: Create or update a storage insight.
      operationId: StorageInsights_CreateOrUpdate
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ResourceGroupNameParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/WorkspaceNameParameter"
        - description: Name of the storageInsightsConfigs resource
          in: path
          name: storageInsightName
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            StorageInsightsCreate:
              value: AzTestSI1110
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ApiVersionParameter"
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/SubscriptionIdParameter"
      requestBody:
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: "#/components/schemas/StorageInsight"
        description: The parameters required to create or update a storage insight.
        required: true
      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK response definition.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/StorageInsight"
              examples:
                StorageInsightsCreate:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/StorageInsightsCreate"
        "201":
          description: Created response definition.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/StorageInsight"
              examples:
                StorageInsightsCreate:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/StorageInsightsCreate"
      tags:
        - StorageInsights

            description: Gets an existing workspace
            operation: Get Workspace

            resource: Workspace
          name: Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/read

            operation: Delete Workspace
            provider: Microsoft Operational Insights
            resource: Workspace
          name: Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/delete

            operation: Get Storage Configuration

            resource: Storage Insight Configuration
          name: Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/storageinsightconfigs/read

          name: Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/intelligencepacks/read

            description: Enables an intelligence pack for a given workspace.

            description: Get search schema V2.
